passages.text: FY25 NPAT a miss vs JPMand consensus; retain Underweight

Key takeaways: 1) Underlying EBITDA loss of \(\) 43m\(was a miss vs JPME of\) \ \(5m\) and BBG consensus of \(\) 17m\(, while Underlying NPAT of\) \ \(173m\) was also below JPME/cons. 2) Net cash of \(\) 248m\(was pre - reported. No dividends were paid. 3) No changes were made to guidance from the JuneQ results. Post - result, our NPV is up\) 8\% \(as we factor in some exploration value (noting the market is willing to ascribe a premium to all lithium plays currently). We note spot lithium is above our base case, and we will look to reassess our S/D outlook post reporting season. We retain our Underweight rating with the stock on a P/NPV of 1.4x.

Results. Revenue of \(\) 513m\(was in - line with JPME/consensus. Underlying EBITDA loss\) \ \(43m\) was a miss vs our \(\) 5m\(and a miss v BBG consensus at\) \ \(17m\) . IGO reported an Underlying NPAT loss of \(\) 173m\(, which was lower vs our\) \ \(87m\) and BBG consensus of \(\) 139m\(. Net cash of\) \ \(248m\) was pre- reported, which came in below JPME and consensus of \(\sim\) 280m. No dividend was paid as expected.

No changes to guidance. No changes were made to FY26 guidance from the June quarterly, with FY26 Greenbushes production of 1.5- 1.6Mt with costs at \(\) 310\(/t - 360/t and Kwinana production expected at 9 - 10kt at costs of\) \ \(16 - 20k/t\) and capex of \(\) 75 - 85m\(. Looking to FY26, priorities outlined include commissioning of CGP3 and completion of life of mine optimisation planning.

Retain Underweight. Following the result our earnings are little changed, but we incorporate some exploration value that sees our NPV rise \(8\%\) to \(\) 3.65\(ps. With IGO continuing to trade at a significant premium to our NPV (P/NPV of\) 1.4x), we retain our Underweight rating. We note spot lithium is above our base case, and we will look to reassess our S/D outlook post reporting season.

IGO is a Western Australian mining company with commodity exposure to nickel, copper and cobalt through the \(100\% -\) owned Nova asset. With its acquisition of stakes in the Greenbushes spodumene mine and Kwinana hydroxide plant, IGO has added lithium to its portfolio of assets. This makes IGO a one- stop stock for EV raw materials. We are Underweight- rated on the stock based on valuation.
Our Jun- 26 price target is derived from our 12- month forward DCF- based valuation, using an \(8\%\) WACC.
